A member of Gombe State House of Assembly representing Nafada South Constituency,  Adamu  Musa, has resigned his membership of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party and joined the governing All Progressives Congress. The member announced his resignation from PDP in a letter dated March 6, 2022, addressed to the party chairman in Birin Fulani West Ward of Nafada Local Government. There has been a gale of defections from both sides lately with the former majority leader, Samuel Markus and Rambi Ayala, defecting to the PDP. The lone female lawmaker in Gombe State House of Assembly and member representing Shongom Constituency,  Asma’u Iganus, has also defected with some of her constituents to the APC. Musa, who is regarded as a highly influential grassroots politician, has already announced his defection to the APC and was welcomed into the ruling party by the Speaker of Gombe State House of Assembly,  Abubakar Luggerewo and other APC lawmakers ahead of his formal reception.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com